Analysis Challenge Assignment 2¶

Author: Ming Chen¶

Introduction¶

I will set 4 sections to complete this assignment
1.clean data
2.find relationships (between independent variables and depend variable)
3.build a classifier (by using the variables that are correlated with on/off-task behavior)
4.evaluate the classifier

# recode the column 'Activity' and 'Ontask'
Adummy=pd.get_dummies(TrData['Activity'])
Odummy=pd.get_dummies(TrData['ONTASK'],prefix='ontask')
TData=pd.concat([TrData,Adummy,Odummy],axis=1)
TData=TData.drop(['ONTASK','ontask_N','Activity'],axis=1)

Interpretation¶

The classifier in the end can hardly predict the correct value.
One possible explanation for the result is that there is no clear relationship between observation variables and on/task behaviors. The indication can be found from the correlation results. There are actually only weak correlations between independent variables and the dependent variable.
I have tried to drop the strange values to clean the data in the dataset, but the result became even worse. I'm not sure where those values come from (maybe they make sense in the real case), so finally decided to keep them.
I have dropped 'FORMATchanges','Obsv/act','Transitions/Durations','Total Time'after doing the correlations, which actually surprised me because I thought they would be important to on/off task behaviors. However, after dropping them, the prediction values seem to be better. It seems that the four variables have little effect on on/off task behaviors, what counts are the types of activity and the indivisual differences (age and gender) of children.
